description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a motivated and hardworking pharmacist to join our rotational pharmacist team as a Band 6 Paediatric Pharmacist for 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join our Near Patient Pharmacy team where you will look after patients on our General Medical wards and General Surgical wards. You will support our operational services (including our in-patient dispensary) and you will be given appropriate training and support to participate in the on-call out of hours pharmacist service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working in paediatric specialities such as cystic fibrosis, gastroenterology and neurology. Experience of paediatric pharmacy is desirable but not essential. Full training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining our supportive and friendly department we would welcome your application. Please feel free to contact Andrew Taylor , Clinical Pharmacy Services Lead (andrew.taylor@alderhey.nhs.uk) or Paul Sanderson, Head of Pharmacy (paul.sanderson@alderhey.nhs.uk)&lt;/p&gt;
